#-Function--implode
  Function: implode
      Desc: Convert array[@] into delimited string.
  Synopsis: implode [-d "delimiter"] "${array[@]}"
          : -d if specified must preceed array.
   Example: str=$(implode -d '|' "${files[@]}")
    Source: /usr/share/okusi/entities/entities.d/entities.version.bash
#-Function--implode-----------------------------------------------------------
